comments.body:
Stack traces are no longer logged for services with missing configuration. We now log warning messages such as:

{code}
Thu May 18 23:31:21 2017  WARN [Topology:eucalyptus-bootstrap-ephemeralconfiguration-bootstrap-topology-external-worker-250] START:DISABLED  arn:euca:eucalyptus:one:storage:one-sc-0/ BROKEN->DISABLED=BROKEN [SC blockstoragemanager not configured. Found empty or unset manager(null).  Legal values are: overlay,das,ceph-rbd]
{code}

{code}
Thu May 18 23:48:00 2017  WARN [EmpyreanService:web-services-worker-pool-23] com.eucalyptus.util.fsm.OrderlyTransitionException: Load failed with error: 'OSG object storage provider client not configured. Found property 'objectstorage.providerclient' empty or unset manager(null).  Legal values are: walrus,ceph-rgw,riakcs', terminating bootstrap for component: objectstorage
Thu May 18 23:48:01 2017  WARN [Topology:eucalyptus-bootstrap-ephemeralconfiguration-bootstrap-topology-external-worker-148] START:DISABLED  arn:euca:bootstrap:API_10.111.5.95:objectstorage:API_10.111.5.95.objectstorage/ BROKEN->DISABLED=BROKEN [OSG object storage provider client not configured. Found property 'objectstorage.providerclient' empty or unset manager(null).  Legal values are: walrus,ceph-rgw,riakcs]
{code}

The output of the euserv-describe-events command should continue to show that the service is not configured when this is the case.
